When (the Apostle) was borne to the presence of God. he said： ‘I know not how
to utter Thy praise.’ Answer came： ‘O Muhammad, if thou speakest not. I will
speak; if thou deemest thyself unworthy to praise Me. I will make the universe
thy deputy, that all its atoms may praise Me in thy name.'
